					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the third pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 20: 926-27 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 90 sheep by Śūlapāṇi Bhaṭṭaśāli, a <hi rend="italic">vaikhānasa</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee in the Vishṇu temple situated to the north of the Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu-mādēvar temple, in Umbaḷa-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
